The Italian coach said he had no reason not to be positive ahead of next week’s Clasico and admitted: ‘Bale was more motivated than usual and the presence of [Luka] Modric helps him. They know each other very well from playing together at Tottenham.'

He will need his talisman Ronaldo back in the right frame of mind before the game however. Last week Ronaldo had to be dragged to the centre-circle by captain Iker Casillas, on Sunday night he ducked out of the post match tradition altogether.

At least next week’s league deciding showdown is away from home.

 

